{"type":"text","timestamp":1775856966189,"sessionID":"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL","part":{"id":"prt_d7952d6b7001W7f423ON9zZdrR","messageID":"msg_d7952ca60001caLMkZvwAP4uYs","sessionID":"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the format. I'll create a proposal.md for AR-014 (Valkey Storage Implementation) following the same structure as AR-013, focusing specifically on the Valkey backend.","time":{"start":1775856966186,"end":1775856966186}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857024887,"sessionID":"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL","part":{"id":"prt_d7952da2e001bpexF7Jo9cWCnK","messageID":"msg_d7952ca60001caLMkZvwAP4uYs","sessionID":"ses_286ad6f16ffesjUNLGKzJUQsJL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_c29755b8d3f54de3a8d567dc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: Valkey Storage Implementation (AR-014)\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the Valkey backend for the session storage interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Valkey storage implementation provides an alternative backend for session persistence in the agentcube project. It enables:\n\n1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information using Valkey key-value storage\n2. **Garbage collection support**: Maintain sorted set indices for expiry and last-activity based cleanup\n3. **Deployment flexibility**: Valkey offers Apache 2.0 licensing and enhanced performance characteristics\n4. **Atomic operations**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` to ensure consistent index updates\n5. **Cluster awareness**: Support for comma-separated addresses and cluster-specific options\n\nThis implementation is the focus of AR-014 and builds upon the interface defined in AR-012, running in parallel with the Redis implementation from AR-013.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n- `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` - Valkey implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n- `sessionKey()` helper function for consistent key construction (shared with Redis)\n- `makeValkeyOptions()` for environment variable parsing and client configuration\n- All `Store` interface methods implemented with Valkey fluent API\n- `DoMulti` operations for atomic multi-command operations\n- `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper using MGET optimization\n- Unit tests with mocked Valkey client\n- Integration tests with real Valkey instance (Docker-based)\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Redis implementation (covered in AR-013)\n- Alternative storage backends (etcd, Consul, etc.)\n- Valkey cluster sharding strategies beyond basic comma-separated addresses\n- Connection pooling tuning beyond default settings\n- Valkey-specific features beyond standard Redis-compatible commands\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Structured logging for client options |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | `SandboxInfo` type definitions |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Store interface (from AR-012) |\n\n### Affected Components\n\n1. **Sandbox Orchestrator**: Will use `Storage()` to persist sandbox metadata\n2. **Garbage Collector**: Will use `ListExpiredSandboxes` and `ListInactiveSandboxes` for cleanup operations\n3. **Session Manager**: Will use `UpdateSessionLastActivity` for activity tracking\n4. **Configuration System**: Must provide `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD` environment variables when `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- This is a new implementation of an existing interface\n- No breaking changes to the `Store` interface\n- Configuration via environment variables (no config file changes)\n- Transparent backend swapping via `STORE_TYPE` environment variable\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Valkey connection failures | Medium | High | `Ping()` method for health checks; connection retry in client library |\n| ZSET index inconsistency | Low | High | Atomic `DoMulti` operations ensure all-or-nothing updates |\n| Password misconfiguration | Medium | High | Clear error messages; `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` escape hatch |\n| Memory bloat from orphaned ZSET members | Low | Medium | List methods tolerate missing keys; periodic cleanup recommended |\n| Cluster slot conflicts in MGET | Low | Medium | Document in code comment; use `ForceSingleClient` option if needed |\n| Cache inconsistency | Low | Low | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` option for cache bypass |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Reuse Redis Implementation\n\n**Approach**: Use the same client library for both Redis and Valkey\n\n**Pros**:\n- Less code duplication\n- Simpler dependency management\n\n**Cons**:\n- Valkey-specific optimizations not possible\n- `valkey-go` library provides better cluster support\n- Misses Valkey's enhanced features\n\n**Decision**: Use dedicated `valkey-go` client library for better Valkey-specific support.\n\n### Alternative 2: Hash-Based Storage\n\n**Approach**: Store session data as Valkey Hash instead of JSON string\n\n**Pros**:\n- Partial field updates without full serialization\n- More efficient for small field changes\n- Native Valkey/Redis type\n\n**Cons**:\n- Complex nested structures (`EntryPoints` array) awkward in hashes\n- JSON marshaling already required for `SandboxInfo` type\n- Less portable if switching to other backends\n\n**Decision**: Use JSON string storage for simplicity and consistency.\n\n### Alternative 3: TTL-Only Expiration\n\n**Approach**: Rely solely on Valkey native TTL instead of maintaining `session:expiry` ZSET\n\n**Pros**:\n- Simpler implementation\n- Automatic expiration handled by Valkey\n- Reduced memory footprint\n\n**Cons**:\n- Cannot efficiently query \"sessions expiring before time X\"\n- Last-activity tracking still requires ZSET\n- Inconsistent semantics between expiry and activity indices\n\n**Decision**: Maintain explicit ZSET indices for efficient range queries required by garbage collection.\n\n### Alternative 4: Lua Script for Atomicity\n\n**Approach**: Use Lua scripts for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` instead of `DoMulti`\n\n**Pros**:\n- True atomic execution on Valkey server\n- Reduced network round trips\n\n**Cons**:\n- More complex code and debugging\n- Harder to test and maintain\n- `DoMulti` provides sufficient atomicity for this use case\n\n**Decision**: Use Valkey `DoMulti` for better code clarity and easier testing.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Details\n\n### Valkey Store Structure\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Purpose | Key Pattern |\n|---------|-------------|\n| Session data | `session:{sessionId}` |\n| Expiry index | `session:expiry` |\n| Last activity index | `session:last_activity` |\n\n### Connection Configuration\n\n```go\nfunc makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n    valkeyAddr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n    if valkeyAddr == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n    }\n    \n    valkeyPassword := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n    passwordRequired := true\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"); strings.EqualFold(v, \"false\") {\n        passwordRequired = false\n    }\n    \n    if passwordRequired && valkeyPassword == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD is required (set VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false to disable)\")\n    }\n    \n    valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n        InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n        Password:    valkeyPassword,\n    }\n    \n    // Optional flags\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if disable, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && disable {\n            valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if v := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if force, err := strconv.ParseBool(v); err == nil && force {\n            valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient = true\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache || valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient {\n        klog.Infof(\"Valkey client options: DisableCache=%v, ForceSingleClient=%v\",\n            valkeyClientOptions.DisableCache, valkeyClientOptions.ForceSingleClient)\n    }\n    \n    return valkeyClientOptions, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Method Implementation Summary\n\n| Method | Valkey API | Notes |\n|--------|------------|-------|\n| `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string | Expect `PONG` response |\n| `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes | Use `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n| `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD expiry`, `ZADD last_activity` | Validate non-nil and non-zero ExpiresAt |\n| `UpdateSandbox` | `B().Set().Key(key).Value(val).XX()` | Response must equal \"OK\" |\n| `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` | Clean up all references |\n| `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix)`, `Limit(0, limit)` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n| `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` on `last_activity` + MGET | Skip missing keys |\n| `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key (must be 1), then `Zadd` | Return `ErrNotFound` if missing |\n| `Close` | `cli.Close()` | Close Valkey connection |\n\n### Atomicity Guarantees\n\n- `StoreSandbox`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for SETNX + ZADD + ZADD\n- `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`: `DoMulti` ensures all-or-nothing for DEL + ZREM + ZREM\n- `UpdateSandbox`: Single `SET XX` command is atomic\n\n### Error Handling\n\n- `IsValkeyNil()` → `store.ErrNotFound`\n- Connection errors → wrapped with context\n- `DoMulti` errors → fail fast with descriptive message\n- Type conversion errors → explicit error message\n\n### ZSET Score Semantics\n\n| Index | Score Source |\n|-------|--------------|\n| `session:expiry` | `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store |\n| `session:last_activity` | `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on store; `float64(at.Unix())` on update |\n\n### MGET Optimization\n\nThe `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` helper function:\n- Builds all `session:{id}` keys from ZSET results\n- Uses single `Mget` command for batch retrieval\n- **Note**: Keys should be in same slot for cluster deployments (documented in code comment)\n- Skips entries where MGET returns empty string (orphaned ZSET members)\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Reference\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses (e.g., `host1:6379,host2:6379`) |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive boolean |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `DisableCache` |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `\"true\"` to enable `ForceSingleClient` |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Must be `valkey` (case-insensitive) for this implementation |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n1. **TestValkeyStore_Ping_Success**: Mock `Ping` returns `PONG`\n2. **TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID_NotFound**: Mock `Get` returns nil\n3. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_NilRejected**: Validate input validation\n4. **TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox_Success**: Verify `DoMulti` commands\n5. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSandbox_MissingKey**: Verify `SET XX` behavior\n6. **TestValkeyStore_DeleteSandboxBySessionID_Success**: Verify cleanup\n7. **TestValkeyStore_ListExpiredSandboxes_Empty**: Limit <= 0 returns nil\n8. **TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity_NotFound**: Missing session\n9. **TestValkeyStore_MGET_ToleratesMissingKeys**: Orphaned ZSET members skipped\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n1. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_FullLifecycle**: Full CRUD operations with real Valkey\n2. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ConcurrentAccess**: Concurrent store/update/delete\n3. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_IndexConsistency**: Verify ZSET consistency after operations\n4. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_PasswordAuth**: Test with password authentication\n5. **TestValkeyStore_Integration_ClusterAddresses**: Test comma-separated address parsing\n\n### Test Fixtures\n\n```go\nfunc newTestValkeyStore() (*valkeyStore, func()) {\n    // Use testcontainers-go or dockertest for Valkey container\n    // Return cleanup function\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `valkeyStore` struct implements all `Store` interface methods\n- [ ] Key patterns match spec: `session:`, `session:expiry`, `session:last_activity`\n- [ ] `DoMulti` operations used for `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- [ ] `ErrNotFound` returned consistently for missing sessions (via `IsValkeyNil`)\n- [ ] Environment variable parsing matches spec table\n- [ ] `makeValkeyOptions()` validates required fields and optional flags\n- [ ] `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs()` uses MGET optimization\n- [ ] All unit tests pass with mocked client\n- [ ] Integration tests pass with real Valkey instance\n- [ ] Code coverage >= 80% for `store_valkey.go`\n- [ ] Documentation includes usage examples\n- [ ] MGET cluster slot consideration documented in code comment\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Interface Definition: `session-store/design.md`\n- Specification: `session-store/spec.md`\n- AR-012 Proposal: `changes/AR-012/proposal.md` (base interface work)\n- AR-013 Proposal: `changes/AR-013/proposal.md` (Redis implementation)\n- Valkey Client Docs: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-014/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775857024874,"end